“A package you selected, or one of its dependencies, requires the latest version of Package Manager to continue with installation. Visit Using Info Codes and enter the Info Code NIPMUpdate for more information.”

I’m not sure of the process to update the Package Manager. Does anyone have any thought on this?

The issue here is that the REVLib package declares that it should be installed by version 23 of the NI Package manager. But no such version has been officially released. I suspect that a development version was given to beta teams that that resulted in this bad reference.

Rev has been contacted, but I have not heard back. Tomorrow I will also find out when a 23 version of the package manager will be released. Either of these paths will result in a working install, but nothing else will. There is no reason to uninstall or take any other action until you either have version 23 of NIPM or a newer version of the REVLib package.

Greg McKaskle
